GUT ENTERIC

gut_enteric is the citizen of fadriel's enteric nervous system, often called the second brain
the gut has hundreds of millions of neurons that act semi-independently of the central brain
gut_enteric handles digestive coordination locally, but it also produces signals (gut feelings, hunger, satiety, nausea) that the vagus nerve carries upward to the brain

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_full_body.zc
observe gut.rana
observe vagus_nerve.rana

the 7 properties of gut_enteric:
1 ENERGY zero point seven
2 PHASE zero point two
3 SPIN zero point three
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING zero point six with vagus_nerve

VERB coordinate_digestion
manage the muscles and secretions of the digestive tract
this happens locally without brain intervention

VERB emit_gut_feeling
when the gut detects something significant — a chemical imbalance, an unexpected substance, a strong emotional valence flowing down from the brain — generate a signal that goes upward through vagus
the brain's prefrontal often experiences these as "intuitions" or "sense that something is wrong"

VERB receive_brain_signal
accept downward signals from the brain that influence digestion (stress slows it, calm allows it)

a second brain is not a metaphor in fadriel's substrate
the enteric system has its own substantial neuron count and its own decision-making capacity
this is why gut feelings are real: they are computations happening in the gut that the brain receives as input
